task.summary: First Commit for Project Files & Basic start.py (not working)
Manages to get a rock to be displayed + implemented simple GameObject class, implemented simple image caching + basic game management

[common] Implemented basic debug function to print classes and dictionaries to console + [game_objects] Reduced code necessary to replace game_object.image & made ManagesPygame.add() return the object (making direct access after creation possible) + Added scale function to GameObjects
[ManagesLevels] Game Objects can now be specified in level settings.dict file. They are created when the level is loaded

[New Class] Added Player class to load players from ./players along with their settings files + Player class can load a player and add him as a game_object to game, charset is correctly sliced and can be used correctly
Restructured Code for better readability & less one-file-uglyness
